verbose_text: When the same analysis was performed on the labra, the mean value for the percentage of lubricin containing cells in the samples with the highly staining ECM was 3-fold higher than the mean value for the samples with the lower levels of ECM staining (24% +/- 13% compared to 9% +/- 7%), but the difference was not statistically significant (P = 0.076, 1 tailed Student t test) owing to the low sample size and variance.
